    <Grid>
        <TextBlock HorizontalAlignment="Left" Margin="63,66,0,0" TextWrapping="Wrap" VerticalAlignment="Top" Height="410" Width="761"><Run Text="When the screen is not displayed at start of the installer"/><LineBreak/><Run Text="The following explains the countermeasures when the screen is not displayed (installation does not start) at start of the installer of this product."/><LineBreak/><Run/><LineBreak/><Run Text="■ Start the installer by the following methods. "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="•  Copy the installer to a directory in a shallow layer such as &quot;C:\temp&quot;, and start it. "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="•  Right-click SETUP.EXE, select [Run as administrator], and start the installer. "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="•  Exit the resident software for a keyboard/mouse, and restart the installer."/><LineBreak/><Run/><LineBreak/><Run Text="■ If the problem cannot be solved by the above method, check whether the personal computer used applies to the following conditions. "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="•  &quot;ntvdm.exe&quot; is high load in the task manager (the usage rate of one CPU core is the maximum). "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="•  The personal computer is equipped with the 6th generation Intel&#xF0E2; Core&#xF0E4; processor. "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="•  An image is output by using the on-board video (CPU built-in). "/><LineBreak/><Run Text="•  Any of edition of 32-bit version Microsoft Windows 7 is used.If any of the above conditions are applied, the Windows system module &quot;ntvdm.exe&quot; may be executed abnormally due to an incomplete BIOS code on the personal computer side, which causes failure to install correctly. Please contact the used personal computer manufacturer, and obtain the corrected BIOS and apply it."/><LineBreak/><Run/></TextBlock>

    </Grid>
</Page>
